	  <abstract>Ver sacrum, or Sacred
	Spring, was the official publication of the Vienna
	Secession.  The title references an ancient religious rite,
	and speaks to the regenerative power of youth in exile. The
	Secessionists had come together in 1897 to oppose the Austrian
	art establishment and pursue a freer, experimental art. The
	journal is replete with original prints by Gustav Klimt
	(1862-1918), Koloman Moser (1868-1918), Josef Hoffmann
	(1870-1956), and others.</abstract>
